The UN-sponsored climate conference -- characterized by far-reaching indiscreet attitudes and mutual scolding -- again on Friday, focused on releasing a document that proposes an ambitious reduction of greenhouse gases over the next 40 years with industrialized nations carrying most of the burden in the near future.
