Experts discuss, for example, when lizards split into three of the most important development lines: carnivorous teropods, which later included Tyranosaur Rex, Velociraptor, and birds, "long-necked" four-legged sauropods and their relatives, and herbivores Ornithischia (birds), such as Triceratops and Stegosaurus.
Tawa hallae is the original terapod after Nesbitt and his colleagues' analysis.
It shows an interesting combination of primitive and advanced properties, says Nesbitt.
Researchers, for example, found evidence of air sacs on the skull of Tawa hallae, which even the offspring of terrapods have birds.
Air bags make bird breathing more effective than mammals.
At Tawa hallae, the bones of the spine were apparently partially filled with air.
Tawa is the oldest and most primitive teropod with air bags, says Randall Irmis.
Since the related line of giant sauropods later also had air bags and light bones, this useful innovation was probably created by a common ancestor of both groups.
